Wake is an exclusive, yet inclusive Coffee & Champagne Bar. Specialty drinks and cocktails are served with style and finesse. Whether you're here for an intimate date or with a group of friends our staff will serve you with hospitality and excellence, The Wake Way.
Our staff is well qualified in the techniques and quality ingredients used to create our crafted drinks; coffee and cocktails. Enjoy an afternoon or evening of charcuterie, high end pastries with your choice of coffee, champagne, wine, or beer.
Our vision was to create an exclusive experience for our community through hospitality while highlighting Charlotte's hidden gem, Mtn. Island Lake.

*Please Check our Instagram for the latest updates regarding liquor, alcohol.

✨ From Set to Style ✨
We're bringing Hollywood to Wake.
Calling all stylists, fashion lovers, and creatives — this is your moment
Join us Saturday, August 2 for an exclusive pop-up with Eulyn Hufkie - the costume designer behind The Walking Dead, Black Box, and more. She's bringing her original, custom pieces and we're turning the space into a fashion-forward showcase for the afternoon.
Shop one-of-a-kind designs
Meet the designer
Sip curated drinks
• Wake Coffee Co. | 2PM- 6PM
Free to attend - RSVP required (link in bio)
Space is limited. — you'll want to be in the room🔥

We’re on the hunt for our next hype girl (or guy)—someone upbeat, dependable, and full of good vibes who knows how to own a shift, solve problems on the fly, and pour a solid latte or cocktail.

If you’re the kind of person who:
	•	Thrives working solo and as part of a small, supportive team
	•	Can follow directions and pay close attention to the little things
	•	Shows up, works hard, and actually cares
	•	Isn’t just looking for a seasonal job—but wants to grow with a company that will value you

Then we want to meet you.

Experience is preferred, but personality, work ethic, and dependability go a long way here. We’re a small but mighty coffee and cocktail bar with hands-on local owners, and when you work for us, you’re not just a number.

Perks include:
	•	Free coffee (duh)
	•	Discounts on food and pastries
	•	Free coworking space
	•	Free venue rental for your next party or pop-up
	•	Creative outlet—we love featuring our baristas’ drink creations
	•	Quarterly team outings & real community vibes

We’re not in a rush. We’re waiting for the right person—maybe that’s you?

To apply, slide into our DMs or email us at HR@wakecoffeeco.com

reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Wanda,
Thank you for taking the time to share your thoughts. We are sorry to hear your experience it didn’t meet your expectations. WCC run by a small team that partners and it’s unclear which owner or staff member you may have encountered— or if it was one of us at all.
We’re proud of our front-of-house team in the consistently warm experience, they provided to each and every guest. 

Your comment about others being treated differently is something we take very seriously. Often, the owners are on site for scheduled meetings or to support behind- the-scenes operations, and while we always try to greet with those who engage with us, we do rely on our front-of-house staff to lead guest interactions during those moments. We’d love the opportunity to learn more about how your expectations could have been met. 

Most importantly, we’d love to know what you ordered—how was your drink? Did you enjoy your experience overall? It’s disappointing to receive a one-star review that seems to stem more from a missed moment of personal interaction than the quality of our offerings. Our team works hard to create a memorable and welcoming environment for every guest, and your feedback on the full experience matters to us.

If you are open to it, we would love to invite you back for a one-on-one with our owners. Please reach out directly to hello@wakecoffeeco.com or by phone 980-949-8865. We look forward to hearing from you. 

With Gratitude, 
Wake Coffee Co. Team

reviews_data.review_text: Good coffee, but completely overpriced. Over $7 for a small oatmilk latte.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
We’re glad to hear you enjoyed our coffee! Thank you for visiting our coffee & cocktail bar.

Our small lattes are priced at $5.25, which reflects the average cost for a quality, specialty latte. The upcharge for oat milk is due to it being a specialty milk, but we do our best to keep our prices competitive and fair.

We’re also not a fast food establishment, and we want to emphasize that—you’re a customer who matters when you walk through our doors. Supporting small businesses requires a bit more effort compared to large chains, whether it’s visiting a single location, working with our hours, or paying slightly more for a personalized experience. We also work with North Carolina state and city taxes, which do impact your total cost.

We understand if chain coffee shops are more suited to your needs, but we hope you’ll continue to support small businesses like ours that take pride in offering custom blends, superb espresso, and a unique experience.  We truly appreciate your support and hope to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: Would not recommend for POC! I love coffee and love trying new coffee shops so it’s such a shame that I could not enjoy my experience here as the coffee actually tastes pretty good (Honey Bee Latte) and the place is super cute, to bad the employees are NOT. I tried this place today, entered in with my kids and one of the workers literally looked at me like she had never saw a black person before. Then as I stood right in front of them at the register (absolutely no one was in there except me and the workers) it took 3 to 4 minutes for them to actually address me and they still didn’t say hello they just said “in the middle of shift change” and continued to take there sweet time to count the money, you could tell they really would have rather me just leave then have to taken my order. There were 3 employees and only one actually smiled when I walked in and I guess when she realized that this was taken beyond too long she decided to go ahead and make my drink while they still prolonged with the register. The barista had literally finished making my drink and they still were sitting there fiddling with the resister giving dirty looks. I got my coffee but won’t be back hate that kind of energy and it’s just unfortunate that my kids had to go through it as well my daughter was so confused as to why no one was talking and things seemed “weird” in there. I’m really big on RASICM  and customer service.
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Dear Symone, 
We are deeply heartbroken to read your review and want to sincerely apologize for the experience you had at Wake Coffee Co. First and foremost, we want to make it clear that we are a woman and Black-owned business, and we do not tolerate any form of racism or disrespect. We take this matter very seriously.

After reviewing the video footage of your visit, we believe the unfortunate situation stemmed from a shift change, during which our team was focused on counting down the drawer. Unfortunately, this caused a breakdown in communication, and we completely understand how this impacted your experience. This was not intentional, and we deeply regret the way it affected your visit.

We want to assure you that this is not reflective of the values we uphold at Wake Coffee Co. We strive to create an inclusive, welcoming environment for all of our customers, and we are committed to providing excellent service.

We would like to extend an invitation for you to visit again, on us, for coffee and cocktails with the owners of Wake Coffee Co. We would love the opportunity to personally meet with you, change your experience, and make things right. If you’d be open to this, please email us at hello@wakecoffeeco.com, and we will be more than happy to arrange a time for you to visit.

Thank you again for sharing your experience, and we are so sorry for the way it made you feel. We hope to hear from you soon.

reviews_data.review_text:
I’m the kind of person that researches menus before going places because I want to know that I have options that support my dietary preferences. I was so pleased to see that Wake Coffee offer Golden Milk with local honey and the option of milk alternatives. I ordered it with almond milk and it was absolutely delicious. You can taste the turmeric and cinnamon and see the sediment of the ingredients at the bottom of the cup; a sign that they use actual dried ingredients and not just flavored syrups.

They also let me use my reusable cup which makes me happy. The shop was playing all the 90s/2000s throw back jams when I visited. It’s clean, comfortable and has multiple seating areas. There is outdoor seating as well. Lots of drink options that don’t involve coffee which is a plus. Service was super friendly. Parking is very accessible and easy.
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you so much for your amazing review! We’re so happy you enjoyed the Golden Milk with almond milk—it’s one of our favorites too! We love that you noticed the real ingredients we use, and we’re glad it made a difference for you. Also, we’re all about throwback jams, so it’s awesome to hear you enjoyed the vibe! It’s great that you felt comfortable and had a good experience with the service, seating, and parking. Thanks for bringing your reusable cup—we love seeing that! Can’t wait to see you again soon!

reviews_data.review_text: I ordered a golden latte and it was disgusting. I can’t even explain how bad it was. I seriously suggest the management to train the baristas on how to make lattes
reviews_data.owner_answer:
Hi Deepu, 

I'm really sorry to hear that your experience with our golden latte wasn't up to your expectations. Our golden milk latte is one of our top sellers, and we take pride in making it just right for our customers.

We checked with our baristas, and they remember serving you and making your drink as you insisted—no sweetener, with just a little honey instead. Any time alterations are made to the original intended recipe, it can significantly alter the taste. We generally don’t recommend drinking turmeric without sweetener as turmeric, as you know, has a very distinct and strong taste and can be overwhelming if not balanced.

Did you have a chance to speak with our barista about your drink when you were here? We always encourage feedback so we can make things right on the spot.

We'd love the opportunity to offer you another latte, as turmeric may not be for you. Please come back in and we’ll make sure your next latte is perfect.

Thank you for your feedback.

I just wanted to take a moment to clarify that our staff is required to make all guests aware of our policy upon entry. This is in accordance with North Carolina ABC Commission laws, which we must comply with as a private bar. Although I understand this may not be the most convenient for everyone, it’s a legal requirement for us as an establishment that serves alcohol, and we are not a typical coffee shop like Starbucks.

We offer a unique space that caters to remote workers, students, and professionals, with high-end conferencing systems available for those who need them. We also offer the convenience of mobile ordering for those on the go, like yourself.

As a small business owner, we strive to comply with all local and state laws, as failing to do so could result in severe fines. To clarify, the law mandates a minimum of $1 annually to hold an ABC license without being classified as a restaurant. So as you can understand the law is non-negotiable.

Again, thank you for your kind words about our staff and decor. We value all reviews, and I wanted to make sure I clarified our position, as it directly impacts my business. I hope you had a great time during your visit to North Carolina!

Warmly,
Wake Coffee Co.

Warmly,
